  • Puritus is common in linear IgA

[!TIP] Mnemonics: 5Ms

  • Military - setting of infection
  • Micro - tiny organisms with no cell wall
  • Minimal lung signs
  • IgM cold haemolytic anaemia
  • Multiforme - Can cause erythema multiforme and nodosum

  • Mycoplasma is one of the smallest known free living organisms.

  • No cells wall -> beta lactams won't work, not visible on gram stain

  • Commonest manifestation is upper respiratory tract infection.

  • but mycoplasma pneumonia is a common cause of community acquired pneumonia as well.

  • Most mycoplasma associated URTI and LRTI are mild and self limiting; They may not even need ABx. Pursuing a microbiological diagnosis usually isn't necessary as management won't change.

  • onset of pneumonia is subacute. Incubation period is 2-3 weeks, in contrast to typical pneumonias which is a few days. Therefore, most common in young adults and children but rare in children < 5 years old.

  • Epidemics frequently arise among persons living in close quarters. (military barracks, schools, households, dormitories)

  • Lung signs on examination are minimal.

    • Because of this, "Chest X ray findings may be worse than clinical features would suggest".
    • Consolidations and hilar lymphadenopathy are rare. Source

  • myocardial: conduction abnormalities (heart block)


- Age of onset in adults is around 50 years
- Most specific rash is the heliotrope rash but it's present only in a minority.
- Gottron's papules : red, scaly bumps overlying fingers and knuckles. May be associated with similar rash on elbows and knees.
- V sign - similar to shawl sign but along the neckline of clothes.
- 20% of those with PM or DM have anti tRNA synthetase antibodies and are more likely to get pulmonary interstitial fibrosis, Raynaud's phenomenon, and "mechanic's hands - roughening and cracking of skin".
- Respiratory muscles are affected -> respiratory failure;
- Oesophageal muscle involvement -> dysphagia.

  • creatine kinase, aminotransferases, LDH and aldolase are all raised.
  • Mainstay of treatment is prednisilone, continued for at least 1 month after clinical and biochemical resolution of myositis.
  • Azathioprine, ciclosporin, cyclophosphamide and MMF are all used as steroid sparing agents.
  • IVIG in refractory cases.

Statin Induced myopathy


Source

  • Need to consider SAMS or Immune mediated necrotizing myopathy (IMNM) in a patient on statins.
  • PMR: Patient it always > 50 years old; sudden onset pain and stiffness (but NOT WEAKNESS) of limb girdles / proximal muscles, associated with raised inflammatory markers.
